OL,3,CLiverpool call for investigation after
OL,4,Cyouth player 'racially abused' twice
OL,6,FLiverpool FC said in a statement that
OL,7,Fthe club "can confirm that a member of
OL,8,Four under-18s team reported he was
OL,9,Fracially abused by an opponent while
OL,10,Fplaying in the Bundesliga Cup youth
OL,11,Ftournament at Schwabisch Hall in
OL,12,FGermany on Friday.
OL,14,F"The player immediately alerted the
OL,15,Fmatch official, his team-mates, and
OL,16,Four coaching staff. Consequently,
OL,17,FLFC's management team decided to stop
OL,18,Fthe game and leave the pitch together.
